name: Museum Sang Hyang Dedari
address: Banjar dinas griana kauh, HF9V+XJ8, North Duda, Selat, kab Karangasem, Bali 80862, Indonesia
review 1: This museum is fascinating. It preserves the Sanghyang Dances, including Sanghyang Dedari dance, which currently is start to difficult to find in some parts of Bali. We came a bit late because around 10 days before our visit, the people celebrating harvesting ceremony where in the ceremony, the Sanghyang Dedari dance is performed in their ritual. It is a small museum but gives rich information on the preservation of the dance. If you visit Bali, I suggest you to come there. However, it is better to contact the officer first.
